<2ND_LINE>PM-Japan-Rainstorm,0096</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rainstorm In Japan Kills Three</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A torrential rainstorm over the Kyushu region of
southern Japan caused flooding and landslides that left three
people dead and three missing in Kumamoto state, police said today.
   They said Masue Zaitsu, 71, Satsuko Kumagai, 57, and Kaoru
Yoshizumi, 79, all drowned during the rainstorm Tuesday night.
   Washed away by a flash flood and still missing were Yuji Ueda,
9; his brother Hiroshi, 3, and Haru Goto, 65, police reported.
   They said flooding from the overflowing Ofuna River also
disrupted transportation in Kumamoto.
