<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--HungryNinja     05-04 0188</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Hungry Ninja,0192</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Seek Snacking Ninja Bandit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gun-toting burglar dressed in black has been
terrorizing residents of a suburban neighborhood, often snacking in
front of his victims, according to police, who call him ``the
Hungry Ninja Bandit.''
   ``He's not doing it for the money,'' Metro Dade Detective Tommy
Robson said. ``He's getting kicks like this.''
   The bandit first struck on Easter Sunday by robbing a home near
Miami Shores. Before he left, he had cole slaw and a glass of tea.
He struck again four days later and two houses away. This time he
ate half a banana before leaving.
   His latest hit was Monday night at the home of Lourdes Orango,
police said. He surprised her in her backyard and marched her
through the back door at gunpoint. Her two children, 11 and 6, were
inside.
   ``While he was there, he called one of his buddies and bragged
about what he was doing,'' Robson said. ``He was laughing about
it.''
   He turned down an offer of a video recorder, but took $60 from
Ms. Orango and two orange sodas, police said.
</TEXT>
