<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Sri Lanka-Crash,0121</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Tain-Bus Collision Injures 35 In Sri Lanka</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A train hit a bus at a crossing near
Colombo today, and police said at least 35 people on the bus were
injured.
   Five of the victims were reported in critical condition, said
police inspector Slavian Mitchell.
   He said the driver of the state-owned bus ignored a red light
and warning bell and tried to beat the train at an unprotected
railway crossing at Narahenpita, four miles outside Colombo.
   ``The driver saw the approaching train and thought he could make
it but did not,'' Mitchell said. Most of the victims were
schoolchildren and office workers, he said. No one on the train was
injured.
</TEXT>
