<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--China-Tornado,0095</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Tornado Kills Five In Southern China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tornado swept through a coastal region of
southern China, killing five people, injuring 40 and damaging
nearly 300 homes, an official Chinese report said today.
   The twister struck Chaoyang county in Guangdong province on
Sunday, carving a path of destruction about three miles long,
according to a China News Service report appearing in Hong Kong
today.
   The casualties included four sisters who were crushed to death
when a building collapsed, the report said. Nine of the injured
were severely hurt.
