<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0384</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Showers Dampen Much of Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Showers dampened much of the nation today following severe
thunderstorms that dropped golf ball-size hail in North Carolina.
   Scattered showers fell from Missouri and Arkansas to North
Carolina and the Mid-Atlantic Coast, with thunderstorms in North
Carolina. Showers and thunderstorms extended from northern Alabama
into southwestern Mississippi.
   Showers also fell over the northern Rockies and scattered
showers fell across the Pacific Northwest. A snow advisory was in
effect for Oregon's Cascade Mountains.
   On Tuesday evening, strong thunderstorms dropped golf ball-size
hail on Cleveland, N.C.
   Clouds and drizzle prevailed over Minnesota and the Dakotas.
Cloudy skies lingered over much of the Northeast and California and
Nevada. The rest of the nation enjoyed fair skies.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
from the southern Ohio Valley to the central Appalachians and
northern sections of the southern Atlantic Coast; scattered rain
showers across the Pacific Northwest, most numerous over Oregon.
   High temperatures were expected to be in the 60s or 70s across
much of the nation; the 50s across the Pacific Northwest; the 80s
from the desert Southwest through the southern Rockies, central and
southern Texas and the Gulf Coast into Florida and the 90s over
desert sections of Arizona and the lower two-thirds of the Rio
Grande Valley.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 26
degrees at Yellowstone National Park, Wyo., to 75 degrees at Key
West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 61 fair; Boston 48 fair; Buffalo 38 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 63 fair; Cincinnati 51 cloudy; Cleveland 44 fair;
Detroit 43 fair; Miami 72 fair; New York 48 fair; Philadelphia 51
foggy; Pittsburgh 47 fair; Portland, Me. 42 partly cloudy;
Washington 52 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 41 rain; Chicago 51 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
58 fair; Denver 41 fair; Des Moines 56 fair; Indianapolis 49
cloudy; Kansas City 54 cloudy; Minnepolis-St. Paul 55 fair;
Nashville 57 rain; New Orleans 66 fair; St. Louis 57 rain.
   _West: Albuquerque 56 windy; Anchorage 43 fair; Las Vegas 64
partly cloudy; Los Angeles 58 partly cloudy; Phoenix 71 fair; Salt
Lake City 49 partly cloudy; San Diego 60 partly cloudy; San
Francisco 50 cloudy; Seattle 44 showers.
   _Canada: Toronto 39 fair.
