<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Soviet-NuclearTest     05-04 0169</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Soviet-Nuclear Test,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Soviets Conduct Nuclear Weapons Test</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union conducted a nuclear weapons test
this morning on the steppes of Soviet Central Asia to upgrade its
military technology, the official Tass news agency said.
   It said the 20 kiloton to 150 kiloton underground blast at the
Semipalatinsk test range in Kazakhstan occurred at 5 a.m. Moscow
time, but did not give the exact power of the blast.
   Twenty kilotons, equivalent to the power of 20,000 tons of TNT,
was the force of the U.S. atomic bomb dropped on Hiroshima, Japan
in 1945.
   This was the fifth Soviet nuclear weapons test this year.
   The Soviets have proposed a moratorium on all such tests, but
U.S. officials have objected because that they disagree with Soviet
proposals on how to enforce the ban.
   A group of Soviet scientists visited Nevada last week to study
ways of verifying U.S.-Soviet compliance with a possible test ban.
In January, American scientists visited the Semipalatinsk range for
the same purpose.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
