<HEAD>Iron Blamed In Baby's Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ENID, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An electric iron that may have been tipped
over by a cat apparently caused a house fire that killed a
3-month-old boy, fire officials said.
   William Loren Ledbetter was pronounced dead at the scene shortly
after firefighters responded to the call, Assistant Fire Marshal
Bill Presley said Tuesday.
   The iron, which was in the infant's room, apparently had been
left on for about three hours, Presley said.
   Ruby Ledbetter told firefighters she was awakened by smoke, but
was overcome as she tried to enter her son's room, Presley said.
   He said fire officials are trying to determine whether a pet cat
might have tipped over the iron.
