<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--All That Loot,0170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>It's Easy Come, Easy Go</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEACON, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``I thought my rainbow had come in,'' George
Wells said.
   There were signs of trouble, though. For one thing, the rainbow
ended in a can of paint, not a pot of gold.
   Wells and Anthony Verdile, both New York State Bridge Authority
workers, were on the catwalk of a bridge over the Hudson River
making a routine check Tuesday when Verdile spotted the can about
30 feet below the road.
   He went climbed down and opened the can to find scads of $20
bills. He climbed back up and found a slight hitch.
   ``As soon as you looked at them you could tell they were
counterfeit because all had the same serial numbers,'' said Verdile.
   Except for that detail, the counterfeit bills were ``pretty well
done,'' said Sgt. Dennis Cody of the State Police after the $39,900
was inspected and counted.
   ``I guess I'll just keep playing Lotto,'' Verdile said.
