<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--China-USTours     05-04 0143</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--China-US Tours,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Chinese Province Planning Tours to U.S.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Southern China's Guangdong province is planning
to organize tours to the United States, but at first it will accept
mainly older tourists who are likely to return home, a newspaper
said Wednesday.
   The U.S. tours could start by the end of the year, the People's
Daily reported.
   It said the first tour will include elderly people with
relatives in the United States. Later, the tours will be opened to
a wider range of tourists.
   China ordinarily issues passports only to people going overseas
on official business or for study programs, but thousands of young
Chinese who have gone abroad to study have either delayed their
return home or decided not to come back.
   The province will send a fact-finding delegation to the United
States to plan itineraries, the report said.
</TEXT>
