   May 2
   Los Angeles Daily News on the Noriega ouster effort:
   The wonderboys from the State and Justice departments had been
acting if they were bullies on someone else's block: They kept
drawing imaginary lines, and Panamanian strongman Manuel Noriega
kept crossing them.
   But finally, as the White House made it known it is willing to
give Noriega an exit that is both face-saving and asset-retaining,
