   _First, the Justice Department indicted Noriega for drug
trafficking. That counterproductive move made it more difficult for
Noriega to retire to countries with which the United States has an
extradition treaty. ...
   _When threats of imprisonment didn't work with the dictator, the
United States switched to using economic sactions as a means of
driving Noriega out. All that did was incur the wrath of the
Panamanian people. ...
   Wouldn't it make more sense to negotiate Noriega out of the drug
trade than hunt him down in the sort of bloody vigilantism that so
resembles American adventurism of an earlier era?
