<HEAD>Album Picture Stolen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The ``Highwayman'' has taken off.
   The original painting illustrating the 1985 ``Highwayman'' album
_ showing Willie Nelson, Kris Kristofferson, Johnny Cash and Waylon
Jennings _ was been stolen Sunday from behind Plexiglas during an
exhibit at the Nashville Convention Center, officials said.
   Allen Brown, a spokesman for CBS Records, said Wednesday the
airbrush picture was valued at more than $10,000.
