<HEAD>Lebanon-Israel At-a-Glance</HEAD>
<HEAD>With Lebanon-Israel Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are Wednesday's developments in the Israeli thrust into
south Lebanon:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   JERUSALEM _ The Israeli military command said the incursion had
ended after two days. It reported three Israeli soldiers and more
than 40 Arab guerrillas killed and 17 Israeli troopers wounded.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   MASHGARA, Lebanon _ Israeli soldiers shelled a Syrian army
garrison earlier Wednesday while armored units drove pro-Iranian
guerrillas from a nearby town and knocked down houses. It was not
clear whether the shelling was deliberate and the Syrians did not
shoot back.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   AIN ATA, Lebanon _ Israeli forces on Wednesday morning searched
Ain Ata and four neighboring villages for guerrillas. Mayor Hussein
Qadi, 70, said an officer told him the Israelis would not return if
``saboteurs'' were kept out of the village, and ``I told him the
guerrillas do not ask our permission to attack Israel.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   MOSCOW _ The Soviet Foreign Ministry called the operation a
``criminal'' incursion that would not increase Israel's security.
