<2ND_LINE>AM-Kissing Bandit,0224</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Awakes With Stab Wounds, Burglar Kissing Girlfriend</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VICKSBURG, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who woke up to find another man
trying to kiss his girlfriend in bed was in critical condition
Wednesday with stab wounds allegedly inflicted by the intruder,
authorities said.
   ``They fought all over that house,'' said Investigator Mark
Culbertson. ``They tore that house up. There was blood everywhere.''
   Anthony Bell, 22, of Vicksburg was being held in Warren County
Jail in lieu of $50,000 bond, facing charges of burglary and
aggravated assault, Chief of Detectives Bob Woods said.
   Raymond A. Barrentine and a friend were asleep at his house
Wednesday when she awoke to find a man trying to kiss her and began
screaming, police said.
   The two men fought, and Barrentine was stabbed at least five
times with a hunting knife before the intruder fled, Woods said.
   Culbertson said there was no indication the burglar knew
Barrentine or the woman. She was not injured, nor was Bell, police
said.
   Barrentine, 33, underwent surgery, and his condition was listed
as critical Wednesday afternoon.
   Police said Bell was captured later in the morning at a
convenience store and the knife they believe was used in the
assault was found at his home.
   Nothing was taken from the house, police said.
</TEXT>
