<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--CouncilArrested     05-04 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Council Arrested,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Entire City Council Arrested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPEZZANO DELLA SILA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The mayor and the five-member
city council of this southern town were put under house arrest
Wednesday after being charged with embezzlement and fraud, police
said.
   The politicians, all Communists, were accused of using public
funds totaling hundreds of thousands of dollars for private
purposes from 1985 to 1987, according to authorities in Cosenza,
the provincial capital.
   Charged were Mayor Fernando Fabiano, 33, a doctor, and
councilmen Francesco Curcio, 32; Francesco Abbritti, 31; Francesco
Mancuso, 51; Emilio Carravetta, 39, and Biagio Martino, 47.
   A spokesman for the Communist party in Cosenza was quoted by the
Italian news agency ANSA as saying that ``further investigation
will prove the groundlessness of charges.''
   The Italian Communist Party is the largest in Western Europe and
has campaigned vigorously against corruption in public
administration, especially in the underdeveloped south.
</TEXT>
