<BYLINE>Michigan Republican Calls for Attorney General's Resignation</BYLINE>
<HEAD>With AM-Meese Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Attorney General Edwin Meese III should resign
in the best interests of the nation, Rep. Carl Pursell, a Michigan
Republican, said Wednesday.
   ``The continued controversy which surrounds Ed Meese is
counterproductive,'' said Pursell, a deputy Republican whip in the
House. ``It has impacted on his credibility, as well as everyone
with whom he is associated. I believe a new attorney general is
needed to restore credibility at the Justice Department.''
   Meese figures in several investigations into allegations of
ethics violations in awards of government contracts, improper stock
ownership and other improprieties.
   The Senate subcommittee on oversight of government management,
whose chairman is Sen. Carl Levin, D-Mich., concluded in a report
that Meese failed to observe an ethics policy in dealings with
Wedtech Corp., a New York defense contractor.
   Pursell's comments were made prior to the report's release.
