<HEAD>New Huey Lewis LP, Tour Schedule Released</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS with 2 grafs to CORRECT that album will be released in
July sted August. PICKS UP 3rd graf pvs, `She said ...'</NOTE>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Huey Lewis and The News announced Wednesday
that they will celebrate the band's 10th anniversary with their
fifth album and a world tour starting this summer.
   The new LP on Chrysalis Records will be called ``Small World''
and be released in July, said publicist Toby Lubov.
   She said the album contains nine original songs and features
guest appearances by singer-pianist Bruce Hornsby, jazz saxophonist
Stan Getz and the Tower of Power horn section.
   The first single will be ``Perfect World'' and is scheduled for
a June release along with a video, Ms. Lubov said.
   A six-week U.S. tour is scheduled to start Aug. 3 in Paso
Robles, with a European tour and a second American leg to follow,
she said.
   The last two albums _ ``Sports'' in 1984 and ``Fore'' in 1986 _
have been multiplatium successes for the six-member group.
</TEXT>
