<HEAD>AGENCIES AND RADIO OUT</HEAD>
<NOTE>For Release Sunday, May 8</NOTE>
<HEAD>From AP Newsfeatures</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-APN--Irving Berlin, b0540-b0541</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   
   NEW YORK (AP) _ Irving Berlin wrote more than 1,500 songs. Here
is a list of some of his most popular melodies:
   ``Alexander's Ragtime Band'' (1911).
   ``Everybody's Doing It Now'' (1911).
   ``When the Midnight Choo Choo Leaves for Alabam'' (1913).
   ``Play a Simple Melody'' (1914).
   ``I Love a Piano'' (1915).
   ``Oh, How I Hate to Get Up in the Morning'' (1918).
   ``Mandy'' (1919).
   ``A Pretty Girl is Like a Melody'' (1919).
   ``All By Myself'' (1921).
   ``Say It With Music'' (1921).
   ``All Alone'' (1924).
   ``What'll I Do'' (1924).
   ``Always'' (1924).
   ``Remember'' (1925).
   ``Blue Skies (1927).
   ``Let Me Sing and I'm Happy'' (1928).
   ``Puttin' on the Ritz'' (1929).
   ``Reaching for the Moon'' (1930).
   ``How Deep is the Ocean?'' (1932).
   ``Let's Have Another Cup o' Coffee'' (1932).
   ``Say It Isn't So'' (1932).
   ``Soft Lights and Sweet Music'' (1932).
   ``Easter Parade'' (1933).
   ``Heat Wave'' (1933).
   ``Harlem on My Mind'' (1933).
   ``Suppertime'' (1933).
   ``Cheek to Cheek'' (1935).
   ``Isn't This A Lovely Day'' (1935).
   ``Top Hat, White Tie and Tails'' (1935).
   ``Let's Face the Music and Dance'' (1936).
   ``I've Got My Love to Keep Me Warm'' (1937).
   ``Change Partners'' (1938).
   ``The Night is Filled with Music'' (1938).
   ``God Bless America'' (1939).
   ``I Left My Heart at the Stage Door Canteen'' (1942).
   ``This is the Army, Mr. Jones'' (1942).
   ``White Christmas'' (1942).
   ``Happy Holiday'' (1942).
   ``You Keep Coming Back Like a Song'' (1945).
   ``Anything You Can Do'' (1946).
   ``Doin' What Comes Natur'lly'' (1946).
   ``The Girl That I Marry'' (1946).
   ``I Got the Sun in the Morning'' (1946).
   ``There's No Business Like Show Business'' (1946).
   ``It Only Happens When I Dance With You'' (1948).
   ``Steppin' Out With My Baby'' (1948).
   ``Let's Take An Old-Fashioned Walk'' (1949).
   ``It's A Lovely Day Today'' (1950).
   ``You're Just in Love'' (1950).
   ``Count Your Blessings Instead of Sheep'' (1954).
