   Texaco Inc. has asked a federal court to freeze
financier Carl C. Icahn's ability to use his stock in moves against
the oil giant, accusing the takeover specialist of ``major
violations of securities laws.''
   The suit, filed Tuesday in U.S. District Court in White Plains,
N.Y., charges that Icahn and others he controls have manipulated
