<TEXT>
   The Air Force has selected General Dynamics
Corp. to build a new unmanned booster rocket to ferry defense
communication satellites into orbit. The contract could be worth
more than $500 million to the company.
   Edward C. ``Pete'' Aldridge announced Tuesday that General
Dynamics had been selected over a competing contractor team
consisting of McDonnell Douglas Corp. and Martin Marietta Corp.
</TEXT>
